social_posts.post_text: My first post in a minute. I laid low for a bit, but time to start engaging again. Inspired here by @frankiefreshcuts  It’s all about the beard of course.

Hold on, we’re coming in for a landing!

“Fresh 24 With Marc Zumoff” debuts Wednesday, April 5th. 

Make sure to subscribe on YouTube and wherever you get your podcasts! See you Wednesday.

“I wanted to stay with the [Sixers]…” @jjredick recounts the offseason following that heartbreaking #Sixers loss to the Raptors. Zoo asks, “what changes if that shot didn’t go in”.

Big thanks to @jjredick for joining this week! Episode is out now!

“When Andre hit those free throws, that was one of the best moments of my basketball career.” 

Former @sixers center @spenceneedle recounts the moments leading up to the upset of the 1-seeded Bulls in 2012, including some clutch free throws from @andre 

Make sure to check out the latest episode now live on our Youtube Channel! Link in bio

#nbaplayoffs #nbafinals
My man @kyleblackstone came to our @maccabiusa golf outing yesterday and delivered healing to those with achy muscles. A big hit!! Thanks Kyle!!
@shappyshaps shows that Philly fandom runs deep in LA and shares experience with Bradley Cooper and others watching Eagles/Sixers games together

“Larry wanted it his way, Allen wanted it his way.” 

Former @sixers president @croce.pat tells a story about @theofficialai3 and Larry Brown and the difficulties of seeing eye-to-eye.

#nbafinals #sixers #alleniverson
I’m here to bail you all out for those last minute Father’s Day gifts. Just tell me what you’d like to tell the old man! Book me on @cameo for that special message!

“Tyrese is gonna be a successful human, basketball player whether he met me or not.”

@Sixers forward @georgesniang speaks about young Sixers guard @tyresemaxey and how their competitive spirit makes both of them better players. 

Make sure to check out Georges' full episode wherever you get your podcasts. 

#sixers #nba

“He was just that kid.”

@mike___jackson tells about his time with @kobebryant and when he played against Kobe in a scrimmage.

Todd MacCulloch on his @tgifridays experience with @theofficialai3 

Former @sixers center Todd MacCulloch describes a hilarious experience with @theofficialai3 at T.G.I. Friday’s.

Todd MacCulloch has quite the hidden talent 

Does @zooplanet have what it takes to match?
#sixers
In his episode, former @sixers center Todd MacCulloch talks about the evolution of the center position and playing with @theofficialai3

“And from then on, I only came with great questions.”

@adamlefkoe talks about his funny interaction with NCAA Coach Rick Pitino and the importance of having confidence in your own players as a coach.
Former @sixers STEVE MIX on the BRAWLS of the NBA
Former @sixers forward Steve Mix talks about the potential roster changes that could and should happen during the 2023 NBA season, including thoughts about @jharden13, @tyresemaxey, and tobiasharris.
Former @sixers guard @tjmcconnell talks about his memorable game winning shot against the Knicks and the atmosphere and energy of the fans during the Process Era.

WHAT IF...Kawhi Leonard misses that shot on May 12th, 2019? Special thanks to my guy @tjmcconnell for coming on the pod.

T.J. believes the Sixers would have won an NBA Championship…Full episode out now…#Sixers #76ers #NBA

I had the hilarious @bigjayoakerson on the pod this week so I had to ask the Philly-born comedian, does being funny really help him get girls?

Big Jay gives us his own personal experience…big thanks to Jay for coming on the pod. Make sure to check out his shows and on tour! #sixers #bigjay #comedy #comedyreels
Comedian @bigjayoakerson gives his opinion on the @sixers chance of winning a championship in the 2023-2024 season and the offseason moves that need to be made to push them to championship-level

40 years ago today, I took this woman to be my wife. Today, her beauty still leaves me breathless. I don’t know what I’ve done to deserve her, but I thank God she’s still with me. Honey, it’s been a wonderful ride so far and still, so much is yet to come. You truly are the best of me.  I say it every day and most especially today, I LOVE YOU❤️
@bigjayoakerson on @andre on the court mentality during his time with @sixers
This one still makes me laugh. The pride of Abington Friends, @adamlefkoe tells us the HILARIOUS story of his second ever show with @shaq on @nbaontnt. Keep making these stories, brother…

Catch the premiere of Season 2 tomorrow!

Season 2 , Episode 1 of Fresh 24 kicks off with Danny Green! Available now on YouTube and all podcast platforms! #sixers #nba

Did you know that Danny Green played QB in High School? Learn more about his choice to pivot from Football to Basketball on this weeks episode of Fresh 24. Available now on YouTube and all podcast platforms! #nba #76ers
On this week’s episode of Fresh 24, Nik Stauskas talks about his accidentally viral nickname “Sauce Castillo” and how this name got him his own hot sauce brand. #sixers #nba
Season 2 Episode 2 with @nikstauskas11 available now on YouTube and all podcast platforms. #sixers #nba
@nikstauskas11 with some high praise for @tjmcconnell on last week’s episode of Fresh 24! #nba #sixers
Philadelphia native and lead singer of Mt. Joy @mattquinnmj joins this week’s episode to talk about the origins of his band and the process of going from student to full time artist. #mtjoy #nba
On this week’s episode of Fresh 24 @mattquinnmj from @mtjoyband talks about his experience with the Sixers as a Philadelphia native. Full episode available now! #sixers #ai

Just how fricken cool is this?

Grow up a Philly sports fan, graduate from Conestoga HS and 12 years later come home for multiple sell outs at The Mann Center and be joined on stage by @jason.kelce. Rockstar stuff from @mattquinnmj and @mtjoyband. Full pod out now!

Handling success is not only a struggle for athletes. In the case of Matt Quinn, musicians deal with a similar phenomenon when they see success and there are many practices artists and athletes put into place to avoid the “yips”. Learn more about Quinn’s journey from law student to world famous musical artist on this weeks episode of Fresh 24! #nba #mtjoy

It’s Tyrese Maxey’s coming out party. Former Sixer @georgesniang saw this coming from a mile away. But also, do Sixers fans owe this success to the Minivan?? 

It’s really special listening to Georges Niang glow while talking about the emerging superstar, Tyrese Maxey on Fresh 24.

Former @sixers head coach John Lucas II joins this weeks episode of Fresh 24! Rebuilding the sixers wasn’t always easy, but during his time Coach Lucas laid the groundwork for a successful era with Allen Iverson! Full episode out Wednesday on YouTube and all podcast platforms! #nba #sixers
“In that game Kobe started out at center, and ended up playing the point guard.” - Former @sixers coach John Lucas II on watching Kobe Bryant in high school. Full episode out now! #nba #kobe

During John Lucas’ coaching career with the @sixers he had to eject one of his own players (BJ Tyler) from a game because of an argument they had court side! Check out the full story in this week’s episode of Fresh 24! #nba

Temple University Head Basketball Coach Adam Fisher shares his thoughts on NIL’s impact on College Basketball on this week’s episode of Fresh 24. Make sure to tune in this Wednesday for the full episode! #collegebasketball #temple

Frontman @mattquinnmj of @mtjoyband dedication to the @sixers is so strong that he actually watches the games before he goes on stage! Check out the full episode to hear more about Matt’s musical journey and Sixers fandom. Available now on YouTube and all podcast platforms! #nba #mtjoy #sixers
Make sure you check out this week’s episode of Fresh 24 with the Head Coach of Temple University Basketball, Adam Fisher. Available now! #nba #templeuniversity

Former @sixers small forward, George Lynch credits Larry Brown’s daughter, Ali with his decision to sign with the 76ers in free agency. Full episode available now on all streaming platforms! #sixers #nba
Philadelphia sports radio icon, Angelo Cataldi, shares his thoughts on cancel culture and its affect on society at large. Check out the full episode available now! #cancelculture #philly

George Lynch, a crucial member of the @sixers during the Allen Iverson era, shares his thoughts on how his 76ers team would perform in the modern NBA. According to Lynch, “Allen would have had his way in today’s game”. Check out the full episode now on YouTube and all podcast platforms #nba #sixers

Can journalists provide analysis on sports they’ve never played professionally? Angelo Cataldi sure thinks so. As a long time sports media figure in Philadelphia, Cataldi talks about how his role as a journalist is pivotal to the sports media world. #nba #philly

Through his decades of working as the play-by-play broadcaster for the @philadelphiaflyers Jim Jackson has had the opportunity to work alongside NHL legend Keith Jones. After recently being hired as the Flyers President of Hockey Operations, Jones has been faced with a lot of doubters because of his role in the broadcasting world, but Jim Jackson is here to reassure Flyers fans that they are in good hands. #nhl #philly

Was the city too harsh on McNabb or was he just a bum?The city of Philadelphia has a long history of treating underperforming athletes poorly, and one of the most famous instances of this was Donovan McNabb getting booed at the 1999 NFL draft after being selected in the first round by the Philadelphia Eagles. #philly #gobirds🦅

Long time @espn anchor and @templeuniv alumnus @kevinnegandhi says that Game 1 of the 2001 NBA Finals was a “top 5 Sixers moment” in the team’s history. Full episode goes live on YouTube tomorrow.  #nba #sixers #espn

Alongside being an accomplished anchor for ESPN, Kevin Negandhi is also a long time supporter of the Special Olympics. His passion for providing individuals with the opportunity to play the sports they love has been a pivotal mission in his career in the sports media world. Full episode available now! #espn #specialolympics
